article.description: John Holland had 25 points and 12 rebounds to lead Boston University to a 79-61 victory over Maryland-Baltimore County 79-61 on Sunday.
article.headline: Holland's double-double leads BU to 6th win in last 7 games
article.linkText: Holland's double-double keeps BU red hot
article.story: BALTIMORE -- John Holland had 25 points and 12 rebounds to lead Boston University to a 79-61 victory over Maryland-Baltimore County 79-61 on Sunday. Jake O'Brien added 18 points as BU (11-9, 6-2 America East Conference) won for the sixth time in seven games by defeating UMBC for the second time this season. The Terriers beat the Retrievers 75-63 on Jan. 12. BU took a 30-19 lead on Carlos Strong's 3-pointer with 2:54 left in the first half and Strong hit another 3 for a 35-23 advantage with 1:18 remaining. Holland made a 3-pointer to push the lead to 40-23 with 19:45 to play in the game. Holland was 5-for-6 on 3-point attempts to help the Terriers shoot 47.8 from beyond the arc (11-for-23). Strong finished with 13 points and Corey Lowe added 10 for BU. Chris De La Rosa scored 18 and Chauncey Gilliam added 10 for UMBC (1-19, 0-7).
